author: @aiswaw6948
text:
Congratulations on your solo debut, Kyungsoo. I love every song in Empathy and my favourite song is still Dad from the first time I watched this highlight medley until now lol. I never changed it coz I really like the sentimental heartwrenching family lyrics in it. And the vocals are always mesmerizing. Kyungsoo always sounded good, even though the music production in this album was very simple but that simplicity brought Kyungsoo's vocals out even more. It matched with Kyungsoo's simple personality/vibe and I love it so much. I really hope and I can also really guarantee that we can get to listen to DKS2 next year at least since Kyungsoo is a bit busier with his acting projects for now. All the best, Kyungsoo. You're a very talented person.

On the other hand, for other EXO soloists, their solo albums are always no skip albums, the same goes for their group albums. I feel so proud. They've come a long way. They deserve all the praises and attention that they're getting now.

text:
Anyone notice the back of the rose keychain has letter and it's different letter in the beginning and ending cut? In the beginning it's "e", in the ending it's "T". Also, the car ignition scene shows letter "p" on the keychain (i think it's different keychain, not the rose keychain). Moreover the flip book got letter "c." on it's cover.
So based on the order in which they appear, we got "e", "p", "c.", and "T".

Does this mean something? I'm not yet think of any good notion.
1) if that keychain is going to be kyungsoo merchandise, and there will be another letter represent "empathy"
2) it is some loophole (cause i notice that the beginning and ending cut is two different cut, since the position of the key in the ground and shooting angle is different. And i also notice loophole about the luggage), BUT what about the letter "p" in the car ignition scene

Garnering all detectives dandanie & exo-l here...

author: @jaehyunsmilk8893
text:
For those who don't understand what this video was about:

D.O was waiting for his flight and he was calling someone while he was waiting. Then he just got up to look at the view. Then a woman bumped into him, because she was in a rush.The had the same suitcase, so when she said "I'm sorry", she accidentally took his suitcase and went away. Then when he got back home from his drive, he drank some coffee. Then he went to go open his suitcase, but he realized it wasn't his. Then he found this notebook and it had the owner's info. So he called her, but she didn't pick up. Then later on, she called him because she had also realized that the suitcase she has wasn't hers. He picked up the phone, and talked about how they would get their suitcases back. Later on, they met up and got each other's suitcases and just chatted while they were going. But while they were talking, he didn't realize that his keys fell. I know this because if you have paid close attention to how his keys looked like at 2:26, they are very similar. But the boy leaves with them because his dad comes and tells him to come with him. 

Hope this helped you understand the concept of this Highlight Melody!  : v )

author: @shortcake.4991
text:
... and I know its a poor attempt of understanding his intention while creating his first solo album, but...

His Highlight Medley (which was released today at 06:00 KST) was very cinematic and visually attractive. More than the love story that the short film was trying to relay, I cant undermine the feeling of connection throughout the story (from the kid who saw and took his key, to the girl who accidentally exchanged their luggages). I came to you now not to analyze the video I saw nor the songs that were initially released but to talk about the poster hanging on his wall (:grin). It was a Nirvana Live at Reading poster! And if you know about the 1992 performance, you'll know that Kurt Cobain sang a line from the Amanda Mcbroom song The Rose. The song was also featured in the ending scene of the 1991 Studio Ghibli film Only Yesterday (wherein the ending theme song was titled "Ai wa Hana, Kimi wa sono Tane", meaning "Love is a flower, you are the seed) or to me: "within me and you, love springs forth". This Japanese animated drama film written and directed by Isao Takahata (which I mentioned previously) was what really piqued my interest. The animation explores a genre traditionally thought to be outside the realm of animated subjects: a realistic drama written for adults, particularly women. 

The lead character finds herself increasingly nostalgic and wistful for her childhood self, while simultaneously wrestling with adult issues of career and love. The story proceeds to forgotten memories, the first stirrings of childish romance, puberty and growing up, the frustrations of math and boys (the same heightened feeling I feel while listening to his track). In lyrical switches between the present and the past, the character  wonders if she has been true to the dreams of her childhood self... after watching the animation, I wonder if he empathizes to the character's sentiments/ thoughts while making his first solo album?

author: @kyungsoodo3288
text:
A letter from Kyungsoo


Dear ROSE,

How are you, MY LOVE? DAD told me you're worried and sad (sigh). I know how hard it is to be away from each other but DON'T WORRY my training will be over soon and we'll get to see each other gain. If CRYING OUT loud will somehow make you feel comfortable and ease, feel free to do it, THAT'S OKAY, but do it once (tease). Do you remember when you TELL ME WHAT IS LOVE? You give and define all the meanings of love. Then you make me feel it and realize how love defies everything. When I haven't met you, I don't believe in love. But the moment I laid my eyes on you, I know IT'S LOVE. Anyway, if you'd ask me, I'm doing good, I'M FINE. So please, stop worrying. There will be no more GOODBYE SUMMER, I promise. Just remember, I'M GONNA LOVE YOU FOR LIFE.

D.O.

author: @ardianaul971
text:
Do Kyungsoo
Izinkan saya menulis setiap kata hati saya yang selama ini saya simpan.
Terima kasih untuk semua kerja keras selama ini, terima kasih untuk tetap bisa bertahan meski tidak jarang hal sulit kamu lalui.  Di saat menjelang tidur, saya selipkan setitik doa untukmu agar kamu selalu sehat dan bahagia. Kyungsoo, tidak mudah untuk saya tetap berada di sisimu sampai detik ini. Kamu yang tertutup, kamu yang jujur apa adanya, kamu yang selalu menyebut kami teman membuat saya sadar diri siapa saya sebenarnya. Tapi bukan itu, syukur saya adalah karena saya mampu mengikuti setiap langkah yang kamu ambil untuk saya jadikan kebahagiaan. 3 hari lagi, hari yang kita nantikan akan segera tiba. Kyungsoo dan suaranya akan terdengar dimana2. Orang2 akan jatuh cinta dengan suara malaikat yang kamu bawa. Saya tidak salah untuk memilih kamu sebagai seseorang yang saya banggakan karena kamu memang pantas untuk dibanggakan. Sedikit cerita tentang hari ini, saya pergi makan bersama kawan saya yang sbentar lagi akan melangsungkan pernikahan. Sungguh saya berbahagia atasnya, saya doakan yang terbaik selalu mengikuti jalan yang ia tapaki. Sedikit sedih di hati saya karena kami akan berpisah, entah dengan jarak atau kebiasaan yang akan jarang kita lakukan. Kyungsoo, jika suatu saat nanti kamu menemukan seseorang yang kamu tatap bisa membuat hatimu berbunga, seseorang yang membuat kamu semakin rajin untuk memasak karena dia sungguh menyukai masakanmu, seseorang yang jika tersenyum membuat kamu tersipu, juga seseorang yang ingin kamu lindungi sepanjang hidupmu. Maka saya ikhlas, berusaha ikhlas untuk melepasmu menuju kebahagiaan. Tapi saya mohon, kamu harus tetap berbahagia menjalani kehidupan.
Kyungsoo, rasanya masih seperti mimpi kamu mengeluarkan album. Hal yang sangat ingin kamu lakukan sejak dlu, hal yang sangat kamu sukai.
Saya menangis, begitu mendengar bait pertama yang kamu nyanyikan.
Indah sekali.
Semuanya indah.
Terima kasih untuk setiap kerja keras kamu.
Bahagia terus ya, Kyungsoo.
Dari saya

author: @mypeaceboy7167
text:
Teruntuk teman rasa suami

Bahan membuat donat:
- 500 gram tepung protein tinggi
- 250 mililiter air hangat
- 100 gram margarin yang sudah dilelehkan
- 5 sendok makan gula
- 2 butir kuning telur
- 6 gram ragi instan
- 2 sendok makan susu bubuk
- Minyak untuk menggoreng
- Gula halus secukupnya

Cara membuat donat:
1. Campur gula, ragi instan dan air. Tunggu sekitar 5 menit hingga permukaan air terdapat buih. Ini tanda ragi dalam kondisi 'hidup' dan adonan nanti akan mengembang.

2. Masukkan tepung, margarin, kuning telur, dan susu bubuk. Uleni hingga adonan kalis atau tidak lengket di tangan dan seperti kembali ke bentuk semula saat ditekan.

3. Letakkan adonan dalam wadah dan tutup menggunakan serbet lembap. Biarkan adonan mengembang selama satu jam.

4. Setelah itu adonan diuleni lagi, ambil sedikit dan bentuk bulatan. Siapkan loyang yang sudah diberi terigu dan letakkan bulatan donat. Sebaiknya diamkan bulatan donat selama 10 menit.

5. Sembari menunggu, panaskan minyak. Sebagaimana dikutip dari Delish, suhu terbaik untuk menggoreng donat sekitar 350 derajat Fahrenheit (sekitar 176 derajat Celcius).

6. Masukkan bulatan donat, tunggu beberapa saat dan balik hingga berwarna cokelat keemasan.

7. Donat yang sudah ditiriskan dan suhunya turun bisa ditaburi gula halus.
